FBIS3-8550 "dreeu049__a94005" FBIS-EEU-94-049-A Document Type:Daily Report 14 March 1994 ANNEX International Affairs Slovakia Welcomes U.S. Initiative on Bosnia AU0903203394 Prague CTK in English 1709 GMT 9 Mar 94 AU0903203394 Prague CTK Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Bratislava, March 9 (CTK) -- The Slovak Foreign Ministry welcomes the proposal to create a Bosnian-Croatian federation as a possible positive impulse for further developments in Bosnia-Herzegovina, a ministry statement handed to CTK on Wednesday [9 March] reads. The statement praises the United States' contribution to attaining the agreement and also the significant role of Russia in the search for a peaceful solution to the crisis surrounding Sarajevo. The ministry favors resolving the crisis in the former Yugoslavia by peaceful means. "We support all processes based on mutual consent, understanding and tolerance. We welcome every initiative which could lead to the ending of the war in Bosnia-Herzegovina," the statement reads.
